    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Camillo Ghilino to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 30 May 1535)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>He is not getting any letters from Oláh these days, although there is
                            someone to take the letters, he thinks this must be due to Oláh’s
                            nonchalance. They have received a letter from Rome, according to which
                            the Pope has appointed six new Cardinals, including John Fisher, whom
                            King Henry VIII is holding in jail. The rest, except for Caspare
                            Contareno, who is above reproach, does not differ from the usual
                            congregation of Cardinals. He voted for the Lutheran bishop from Paris
                            to favor the French, he knows the rest. The imperial fleet consists of
                            330 boats, and Lucretia Caballis will tell him about the Turkish
                            affairs. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Idem Nicolao Olao salutem. </p>
                <p>Iam aliquot dies sunt, ex quo nullas tuas litteras accepimus, quod puto
                    negligentia tua factum esse. Nam tu, qui in otio es, quid est, quod omnes ferme
                    tabellarios ab hinc duos menses ad nos venientes praeteristi sine litteris tuis.
                    Noli, amabo, Olae Carissime, hac mecum taciturnitate uti, et de rebus vestris
                    fac me et de statu rerum tuarum frequenter certiorem. Ex litteris Urbanis
                    intelleximus <persName>pontificem</persName><note type="critic">Pope Paul
                        III.</note> VI cardinales designasse,<note type="critic">In the second
                        Consistory for the promotion of cardinals, Pope Paul III created seven
                        cardinals: Nicolaus Schönberg, Hieronymus de Ginutiis, Jacobus Simoneta,
                        Johannes Fisher, Johannes de Bellayo, Gasparus Contarenus and Marinus
                        Ascanius de Carraciolis. See <hi rend="smallcap">Van Gulik–Eubel</hi> 1923,
                        23–24; and <hi rend="smallcap">De Vocht</hi> 1961, 241.</note> inter quos
                    habetis <persName>episcopum Ruffensem</persName>,<note type="critic">John
                        Fisher.</note> quem <persName>rex Anglus</persName><note type="critic">King
                        Henry VIII.</note>
                    <choice>
                        <orig>vir sane bonus et intelligens</orig>
                        <supplied>virum sane bonum et intelligentem</supplied>
                    </choice> in carceribus habet.<note type="critic">He was executed not much
                        later, on 22 June, 1535, at the order of King Henry VIII.</note> Reliqui,
                    excepto <persName>Contareno patricio Veneto</persName><note type="critic"
                        >Caspare Contareno or Gasparo Contarini (†1542) was Apostolic Legat and
                        Cardinal, and he wrote the book <hi rend="italic">De magistratibus et
                            republica Venetorum libri quinque</hi> (Veneto, 1551), see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">De Vocht</hi> 1961, 241, 267–268.</note> philosopho et
                    theologo, vitae integritate cum paucis conferendo, ab consueto cardinalium coetu
                    non degenerant. In Gallorum gratia elegit <persName>episcopum
                        Parisiensem</persName><note type="critic">Jean du Bellay (1492–1560) was
                        Bishop of Paris from 1532.</note> Lutheranum, cetera nosti. Classis caesaris
                    CCCXXX navium erit, apparatus ingens. Res Turcicas intelliges de
                        <persName>Lucretia</persName><note type="critic">Lucretia Caballis (vom
                        Ross).</note> nostra. Tu vale et <persName>Sceppero</persName><note
                        type="critic">Cornelis de Schepper.</note> nostro me commenda. </p>
                <p><placeName>Mediolano</placeName> XXX. Maii MDXXXV.</p>
            </div>
